\pard\plain \ltrch\loch {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The region is relatively wealthy and prosperous, as compared to bordering regions like Weshewen, Lewshanana, Krbshanana, the Forg and even Aranzen.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 FARMING}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A key reason why so many non-humans stay in Saskantinon despite its somewhat confusing and even harsh political environment is }{\f0\fs24\b1\i0\cf1 agriculture}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  does well in the region. And this is due almost entirely to the fact that the Herbalists have learned to take the place of birds and bees and this knowledge is widespread throughout the Lands.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  Nearly all of the towns and villages in the area maintain farming operations at one level or another of technological advancement.  Many farmers are free-holders. In the south, the Herbalist Federation acts as a kind of farmers cooperative. Many others are more-or-less vassals who work to support the nearest town and its institutions.  While the technological level is fairly rudimentary in many areas, the land is fertile enough to support a variety of techniques. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Domesticated non-sint livestock for milk and cloth (fur) materials is fairly common. Using livestock for food is less common and somewhat controversial, especially in certain areas.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mammalian meat plays a considerably smaller role in Saskan life than it does in our world. Both pigs and cows have sint and mixed \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93cousins\u8221\'94 who look very unkindly on eating their \u8220\'93relatives\u8221\'94 and feel it  is a threat.  There are no avians of any type, hence no chickens, etc.  Most meat-eating is aimed at fish, reptiles and insects.   }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 LAND}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Land ownership is seldom private and individual. Where it is not in the trust of a local organization or guild or tribe or clan, it is often held by a collective of some kind and treated as something like a common resource.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 HUNTING and FISHING}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 The also region also supports a lot of grazing and hunting, especially in the north.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 It supports both a pastoral and nomadic economies, though nomadic/travelling bands are less common than settled ones. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Domesticated livestock is common in the human regions of the north, though it is also the source of ongoing disputes and even sometimes violent conflicts between animal-liberationists and human-supremacists.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 A variety of wild beasts who are }{\f1\fs24\b0\i1\cf1 not}{\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1  sentient \endash  in the sense that they do not use tools, use a language intelligible to other species, create urban or village centers, or develop an oral or written literature \endash  roam the plains and mountains, especially in the northern, eastern and southern regions outside of the Ring. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Hunting expeditions, almost always \endash  but not exclusively \endash  organized by humans or human-appearing guilders, constantly work these areas.  They gather and hunt in the western mountains and rivers too, although there tends to be less available prey in those areas. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Fishing is common in both rivers and seas, with occasional disruptions from water-resident sints.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Fishing and sea-going trades are very common in the East, especially. As with hunting, this type of work can be fraught with difficulties and conflict due to the large number of fully-sentient animals inhabiting the Delta of Lewshanana as well as the Krbshsea itself.  Typically, they themselves are consumers of seafood, so it can be a little confusing \hich\f0 \emdash \loch\f0  more a matter of competition than an ethical question.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 MINING}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Mining operations are located mainly in the western mountains, as well as near the marshy Krbshsea shoreline of the southeastern Oobar-speaking region.  }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 MANUFACTURING}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Most manufacturing is at a fantasy-world-medieval level, with a focus on small-scale handicraft. There are few large manufactories, though some do exist. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Common types of goods include:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Prepared foods, food ingredients}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Prepared and fermented beverages}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Weapons and Armor}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Clothing and fabrics}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Conveyances (wagons, boats, and so on)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Tools and Hardware}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Rope and Sails}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Cut stone and wood}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Medicines and psycho-active substances}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Musical instruments}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Scrolls, parchments, books and writing materials}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Pigments and brushes}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Candles, Lamps and Reflective surfaces (mirrors)}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Utensils and Containers}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b1\i0\ul\ulc0\cf1 SERVICES}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 With the exception of agricultural goods, the provisioning of goods and services is dominated by guild monopolies, though there are competing guilds and geographical variations. }
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 See notes below on Trade.}
\par\plain \f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 Key \loch\af0\hich\af0\dbch\af0\uc1\u8220\'93service industries\u8221\'94 are also coordinated through guilds, though some are very loose. These include:}
\par\plain {\f0\fs24\b0\i0\cf1 - Scribes}
